#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:4
msgid "Media Subsystem Profile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:7
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:9
msgid ""
"The Linux Media Community (aka: the LinuxTV Community) is formed by "
"developers working on Linux Kernel Media Subsystem, together with users who "
"also play an important role in testing the code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:13
msgid ""
"The Media Subsystem has code to support a wide variety of media-related "
"devices: stream capture, analog and digital TV streams, cameras, video "
"codecs, video processing (resizers, etc.), radio, remote controllers, HDMI "
"CEC and media pipeline control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:18
msgid ""
"The Media Subsystem consists of the following directories in the kernel tree:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:21
msgid "drivers/media"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:22
msgid "drivers/staging/media"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:23
msgid "include/media"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:24
msgid "Documentation/devicetree/bindings/media/\\ [1]_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:25
msgid "Documentation/admin-guide/media"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:26
msgid "Documentation/driver-api/media"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:27
msgid "Documentation/userspace-api/media"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:29
msgid ""
"Device tree bindings are maintained by the OPEN FIRMWARE AND FLATTENED "
"DEVICE TREE BINDINGS maintainers (see the MAINTAINERS file). So, changes "
"there must be reviewed by them before being merged into the media "
"subsystem's development tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:35
msgid ""
"Both media userspace and Kernel APIs are documented and the documentation "
"must be kept in sync with the API changes. It means that all patches that "
"add new features to the subsystem must also bring changes to the "
"corresponding API documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:41
msgid "Media Maintainers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:43
msgid ""
"Media Maintainers are not just people capable of writing code, but they are "
"developers who have demonstrated their ability to collaborate with the team, "
"get the most knowledgeable people to review code, contribute high-quality "
"code, and follow through to fix issues (in code or tests)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:48
msgid ""
"Due to the size and wide scope of the media subsystem, multiple layers of "
"maintainers are required, each with their own areas of expertise:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:51
msgid "**Media Driver Maintainer**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:52
msgid ""
"Responsible for one or more drivers within the Media Subsystem. They are "
"listed in the MAINTAINERS file as maintainer for those drivers. Media Driver "
"Maintainers review patches for those drivers, provide feedback if patches do "
"not follow the subsystem rules, or are not using the media kernel or "
"userspace APIs correctly, or if they have poor code quality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:59
msgid ""
"If you are the patch author, you work with other Media Maintainers to ensure "
"your patches are reviewed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:62
msgid ""
"Some Media Driver Maintainers have additional responsibilities. They have "
"been granted Patchwork access and keep `Patchwork <https://patchwork.linuxtv."
"org/project/linux-media/list/>`_ up to date, decide when patches are ready "
"for merging, and create Pull Requests for the Media Subsystem Maintainers to "
"merge."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:68
msgid "**Media Core Maintainer**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:69
msgid ""
"Media Driver Maintainers with Patchwork access who are also responsible for "
"one or more media core frameworks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:72
msgid ""
"Core framework changes are done via consensus between the relevant Media "
"Core Maintainers. Media Maintainers may include core framework changes in "
"their Pull Requests if they are signed off by the relevant Media Core "
"Maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:77
msgid "**Media Subsystem Maintainers**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:78
msgid ""
"Media Core Maintainers who are also responsible for the subsystem as a "
"whole, with access to the entire subsystem. Responsible for merging Pull "
"Requests from other Media Maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:82
msgid ""
"Userspace API/ABI changes are made via consensus among Media Subsystem "
"Maintainers\\ [2]_. Media Maintainers may include API/ABI changes in their "
"Pull Requests if they are signed off by all Media Subsystem Maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:87
msgid ""
"All Media Maintainers shall agree with the Kernel development process as "
"described in Documentation/process/index.rst and with the Kernel development "
"rules in the Kernel documentation, including its code of conduct."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:91
msgid ""
"Media Maintainers are often reachable via the #linux-media IRC channel at "
"OFTC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:93
msgid ""
"Everything that would break backward compatibility with existing non-kernel "
"code are API/ABI changes. This includes ioctl and sysfs interfaces, v4l2 "
"controls, and their behaviors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:98
msgid "Patchwork Access"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:100
msgid ""
"All Media Maintainers who have been granted Patchwork access shall ensure "
"that `Patchwork <https://patchwork.linuxtv.org/project/linux-media/list/>`_ "
"will reflect the current status, e.g. patches shall be delegated to the "
"Media Maintainer who is handling them and the patch status shall be updated "
"according to these rules:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:106
msgid ""
"``Under Review``: Used if the patch requires a second opinion or when it is "
"part of a Pull Request;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:108
msgid ""
"``Superseded``: There is a newer version of the patch posted to the mailing "
"list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:110
msgid ""
"``Duplicated``: There was another patch doing the same thing from someone "
"else that was accepted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:112
msgid ""
"``Not Applicable``: Use for patch series that are not merged at media.git "
"tree (e.g. drm, dmabuf, upstream merge, etc.) but were cross-posted to the "
"linux-media mailing list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:115
msgid ""
"``Accepted``: Once a patch is merged in the multi-committer tree. Only Media "
"Maintainers with commit rights are allowed to set this state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:118
msgid ""
"If Media Maintainers decide not to accept a patch, they should reply to the "
"patch authors by e‑mail, explaining why it is not accepted, and update "
"`Patchwork <https://patchwork.linuxtv.org/project/linux-media/list/>`_ "
"accordingly with one of the following statuses:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:123
msgid "``Changes Requested``: if a new revision was requested;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:124
msgid "``Rejected``: if the proposed change is not acceptable at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:128
msgid ""
"Patchwork supports a couple of clients to help semi-automate status updates "
"via its REST interface:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:131
msgid "https://patchwork.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage/clients/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:133
msgid ""
"For patches that fall within their area of responsibility a Media Maintainer "
"also decides when those patches are ready for merging, and create Pull "
"Requests for the Media Subsystem Maintainers to merge."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:137
msgid ""
"The most important aspect of becoming a Media Maintainer with Patchwork "
"access is that you have demonstrated an ability to give good code reviews. "
"We value your ability to deliver thorough, constructive code reviews."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:141
msgid ""
"As such, potential maintainers must earn enough credibility and trust from "
"the Linux Media Community. To do that, developers shall be familiar with the "
"open source model and have been active in the Linux Kernel community for "
"some time, and, in particular, in the media subsystem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:146
msgid ""
"In addition to actually making the code changes, you are basically "
"demonstrating your:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:149
msgid "commitment to the project;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:150
msgid "ability to collaborate with the team and communicate well;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:151
msgid ""
"understanding of how upstream and the Linux Media Community work (policies, "
"processes for testing, code review, ...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:153
msgid "reasonable knowledge about:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:155
msgid "the Kernel development process: Documentation/process/index.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:158
msgid ""
"the Media development profile: Documentation/driver-api/media/maintainer-"
"entry-profile.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:161
msgid "understanding of the projects' code base and coding style;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:162
msgid "ability to provide feedback to the patch authors;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:163
msgid "ability to judge when a patch might be ready for review and to submit;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:164
msgid "ability to write good code (last but certainly not least)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:166
msgid ""
"Media Driver Maintainers that desire to get Patchwork access are encouraged "
"to participate at the yearly Linux Media Summit, typically co-located with a "
"Linux-related conference. These summits are announced on the linux-media "
"mailing list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:171
msgid ""
"If you are doing such tasks and have become a valued developer, an existing "
"Media Maintainer can nominate you to the Media Subsystem Maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:174
msgid ""
"The ultimate responsibility for accepting a nominated maintainer is up to "
"the subsystem's maintainers. The nominated maintainer must have earned a "
"trust relationship with all Media Subsystem Maintainers, as, by being "
"granted Patchwork access, you will take over part of their maintenance tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:180
msgid "Media Committers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:182
msgid ""
"Experienced and trusted Media Maintainers may be granted commit rights which "
"allow them to directly push patches to the media development tree instead of "
"posting a Pull Request for the Media Subsystem Maintainers. This helps "
"offloading some of the work of the Media Subsystem Maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:187
msgid ""
"More details about Media Committers' roles and responsibilities can be found "
"here: :ref:`Media Committers`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:191
msgid "Media development sites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:193
msgid ""
"The `LinuxTV <https://linuxtv.org/>`_ web site hosts news about the "
