#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:220
msgid "Media development workflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:222
msgid ""
"All changes for the media subsystem shall be sent first as e-mails to the "
"media mailing list, following the process documented at Documentation/"
"process/index.rst."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:226
msgid ""
"It means that patches shall be submitted as plain text only via e-mail to "
"linux-media@vger.kernel.org (aka: LMML). While subscription is not "
"mandatory, you can find details about how to subscribe to it and to see its "
"archives at:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:230
msgid "https://subspace.kernel.org/vger.kernel.org.html"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:232
msgid "Emails with HTML will be automatically rejected by the mail server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:234
msgid ""
"It could be wise to also copy the relevant Media Maintainer(s). You should "
"use ``scripts/get_maintainers.pl`` to identify whom else needs to be copied. "
"Please always copy driver's authors and maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:238
msgid ""
"To minimize the chance of merge conflicts for your patch series, and make it "
"easier to backport patches to stable Kernels, we recommend that you use the "
"following baseline for your patch series:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:242
msgid "Features for the next mainline release:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:244
msgid "baseline shall be the ``media-committers.git next`` branch;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:246
msgid "Bug fixes for the next mainline release:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:248
msgid ""
"baseline shall be the ``media-committers.git next`` branch. If the changes "
"depend on a fix from the ``media-committers.git fixes`` branch, then you can "
"use that as baseline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:252
msgid "Bug fixes for the current mainline release (-rcX):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:254
msgid ""
"baseline shall be the latest mainline -rcX release or the ``media-committers."
"git fixes`` branch if changes depend on a mainline fix that is not yet "
"merged;"
