#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:266
msgid "when applicable, a ``Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:268
msgid ""
"Patches that were fixing bugs publicly reported by someone at the linux-"
"media@vger.kernel.org mailing list shall have:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:271
msgid "a ``Reported-by:`` tag immediately followed by a ``Closes:`` tag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:273
msgid ""
"Patches that change API shall update documentation accordingly at the same "
"patch series."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:276
msgid ""
"See Documentation/process/index.rst for more details about e-mail submission."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:278
msgid ""
"Once a patch is submitted, it may follow either one of the following "
"workflows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:281
msgid ""
"Media Maintainers' workflow: Media Maintainers post the Pull Requests, which "
"are handled by the Media Subsystem Maintainers::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:290
msgid ""
"For this workflow, Pull Requests are generated by Media Maintainers with "
"Patchwork access.  If you do not have Patchwork access, then please don't "
"submit Pull Requests, as they will not be processed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:294
msgid ""
"Media Committers' workflow: patches are handled by Media Maintainers with "
"commit rights::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:302
msgid ""
"When patches are picked up by `Patchwork <https://patchwork.linuxtv.org/"
"project/linux-media/list/>`_ and when merged at media-committers, Media CI "
"bots will check for errors and may provide e-mail feedback about patch "
"problems. When this happens, the patch submitter must fix them or explain "
"why the errors are false positives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:308
msgid ""
"Patches will only be moved to the next stage in these two workflows if they "
"pass on Media CI or if there are false-positives in the Media CI reports."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:311
msgid ""
"For both workflows, all patches shall be properly reviewed at linux-"
"media@vger.kernel.org (LMML) before being merged in ``media-committers."
"git``. Media patches will be reviewed in a timely manner by the maintainers "
"and reviewers as listed in the MAINTAINERS file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:316
msgid ""
"Media Maintainers shall request reviews from other Media Maintainers and "
"developers where applicable, i.e. because those developers have more "
"knowledge about some areas that are changed by a patch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:320
msgid ""
"There shall be no open issues or unresolved or conflicting feedback from "
"anyone. Clear them up first. Defer to the Media Subsystem Maintainers if "
"needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:325
msgid "Failures during e-mail submission"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:327
msgid ""
"Media's workflow is heavily based on Patchwork, meaning that, once a patch "
"is submitted, the e-mail will first be accepted by the mailing list server, "
"and, after a while, it should appear at:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:331
msgid "https://patchwork.linuxtv.org/project/linux-media/list/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:333
msgid ""
"If it doesn't automatically appear there after some time [3]_, then probably "
"something went wrong on your submission. Please check if the email is in "
"plain text\\ [4]_ only and if your emailer is not mangling whitespaces "
"before complaining or submitting them again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:338
msgid ""
"To troubleshoot problems, you should first check if the mailing list server "
"has accepted your patch, by looking at:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:341
msgid "https://lore.kernel.org/linux-media/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:343
msgid ""
"If the patch is there and not at `Patchwork <https://patchwork.linuxtv.org/"
"project/linux-media/list/>`_, it is likely that your e-mailer mangled the "
"patch. Patchwork internally has logic that checks if the received e-mail "
"contains a valid patch. Any whitespace and new line breakages mangling the "
"patch won't be recognized by `Patchwork <https://patchwork.linuxtv.org/"
"project/linux-media/list/>`_, and such a patch will be rejected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:351
msgid ""
"It usually takes a few minutes for the patch to arrive, but the e-mail "
"server may be busy, so it may take a longer time for a patch to be picked by "
"`Patchwork <https://patchwork.linuxtv.org/project/linux-media/list/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:356
msgid ""
"If your email contains HTML, the mailing list server will simply drop it, "
"without any further notice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:362
msgid "Authentication for pull and merge requests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:364
msgid ""
"The authenticity of developers submitting Pull Requests and merge requests "
"shall be validated by using the Linux Kernel Web of Trust, with PGP signing "
"at some moment. See: :ref:`kernel_org_trust_repository`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:368
msgid ""
"With the Pull Request workflow, Pull Requests shall use PGP-signed tags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:370
msgid ""
"With the committers' workflow, this is ensured at the time merge request "
"rights will be granted to the gitlab instance used by the media-committers."
"git tree, after receiving the e-mail documented in :ref:`media-committer-"
"agreement`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:375
msgid ""
"For more details about PGP signing, please read Documentation/process/"
"maintainer-pgp-guide.rst."
