#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:476
msgid "Style Cleanup Patches"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:478
msgid ""
"Style cleanups are welcome when they come together with other changes at the "
"files where the style changes will affect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:481
msgid ""
"We may accept pure standalone style cleanups, but they should ideally be one "
"patch for the whole subsystem (if the cleanup is low volume), or at least be "
"grouped per directory. So, for example, if you're doing a big cleanup change "
"set at drivers under drivers/media, please send a single patch for all "
"drivers under drivers/media/pci, another one for drivers/media/usb and so on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:489
msgid "Coding Style Addendum"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:491
msgid ""
"Media development uses ``checkpatch.pl`` on strict mode to verify the code "
"style, e.g.::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:496
msgid ""
"In principle, patches should follow the coding style rules, but exceptions "
"are allowed if there are good reasons. On such case, maintainers and "
"reviewers may question about the rationale for not addressing the "
"``checkpatch.pl``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:500
msgid ""
"Please notice that the goal here is to improve code readability. On a few "
"cases, ``checkpatch.pl`` may actually point to something that would look "
"worse. So, you should use good sense."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:504
msgid ""
"Note that addressing one ``checkpatch.pl`` issue (of any kind) alone may "
"lead to having longer lines than 80 characters per line. While this is not "
"strictly prohibited, efforts should be made towards staying within 80 "
"characters per line. This could include using re-factoring code that leads "
"to less indentation, shorter variable or function names and last but not "
"least, simply wrapping the lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:511
msgid "In particular, we accept lines with more than 80 columns:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:513
msgid "on strings, as they shouldn't be broken due to line length limits;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:514
msgid ""
"when a function or variable name needs to have a long identifier name, which "
"makes hard to honor the 80 columns limit;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:516
msgid ""
"on arithmetic expressions, when breaking lines makes them harder to read;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:518
msgid ""
"when they avoid a line ending with an open parenthesis or an open bracket."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:522
msgid "Key Cycle Dates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:524
msgid ""
"New submissions can be sent at any time, but if they are intended to hit the "
"next merge window they should be sent before -rc5, and ideally stabilized in "
"the linux-media branch by -rc6."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:529
msgid "Review Cadence"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:531
msgid ""
"Provided that your patch has landed in `Patchwork <https://patchwork.linuxtv."
"org/project/linux-media/list/>`_, it should be sooner or later handled, so "
"you don't need to re-submit a patch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:535
msgid ""
"Except for important bug fixes, we don't usually add new patches to the "
"development tree between -rc6 and the next -rc1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:538
msgid ""
"Please notice that the media subsystem is a high traffic one, so it could "
"take a while for us to be able to review your patches. Feel free to ping if "
"you don't get a feedback in a couple of weeks or to ask other developers to "
"publicly add ``Reviewed-by:`` and, more importantly, ``Tested-by:`` tags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/maintainer-entry-profile.rst:544
msgid ""
"Please note that we expect a detailed description for ``Tested-by:``, "
"identifying what boards were used during the test and what it was tested."
msgstr ""
